 bard recently come to be a member of CB.  Lately I've been doing little things here and there in order to get pieces of my epic done as soon as I can.  Have done some things solo, while others were with the help of guildmates, such as the daylong raid to kill Phinny, and the killing of Maligar in WK with the help of Ferir and Weetang.  The point is that in the future, things are only going to become more difficult and I will need more and more help from the guild to accomplish things.  I hope by posting this I can give everyone a better understanding of what is needed to accomplish these goals which in the end will help the guild become stronger.  At this point, I have 2 of the final 4 pieces needed for my epic, but they are by far the easiest to get.  As for whats left... heres a short list of the things I will need to accomplish:<br>1. Find and kill two named dragons in kunark for a no drop item off them both. (Eldrig the Old, 51, Skyfire mountains, and Nezekezena, 51, Burning Woods)<br>2. Kill Phinigel Atropos until he decides to drop his spine.<br>3. Group to kill/loot petrified lycanthrope skull off of the drolvarg warlord in KC.<br>4. Obtain a white and red dragon scale. (white from either Vox or Gorenaire, Red from Nagafen, Nortlav the scalekeeper, or another red dragon from kunark)<br>5. Last but not least, we need to kill Trakanon.  Twice.  When he is first killed and undead bard will spawn and upon giving him a quest item he will need to be killed and then a Trak clone will pop with the same stats/skills of the original.  The clone is the only one that drops the guts I need to complete my epic.<br>Looking at all this it seems that we have our work cut out for us, and this is only one of many epics in our guild.  I hope that I will be able to depend on you all when the time comes to attempt one of these pieces.  I hope to be there if at all possible when the time comes to help you on any part of your Epic, I will be there and so will those who you have helped work on their epics will be as well.  Above all, this will help us become more familiar with each others skills and as guildmates.<br><br>Here are the stats on my epic and its effect, as you can see I think that short of a click stick or the staff of the serpent, this is probably the best guild oriented epic out there.<br><br>Singing Short Sword: 16/26 1hs 15 str 10 dex 5 sta 20 cha 100 hps 10 sv all effect: dance of the blade (group 55% haste, 30 str 30 atk, haste stacks with all other hastes and lets you exceed the haste cap)<br><br>I hope to see some feedback on this and hope to see others post as well about their epics.  This way we can all become more familiar with what needs to be done.<br><br>Kirus Atraides<br>Bard of the 47th song<br>Prankster of Bristlebane<br>&quot;You think you're fast? Try chasing a bard.  Then again, try me and we'll see how well you run from one&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8B0000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ucrazysagedancer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>crazysagedancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/27/02 12:51:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fchosenblood23740frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Epics</span><hr size=1> sounds like fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  im apporaching a level where I can help out more.  <br>If not able to come and hunt, I will port<br>only think is, dont assume i will port ask first<br>There has been like two times where I have refused to port someone.<br>Xeela Moopuppy<br>*ps i dont have gd port...would love anyone forever if they picked it up for me in wakening lands...dont have that one